Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Trim the @carrot{1} then halve lengthways (no need to
peel). Thinly slice widthways.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1 bunch}(stalks and all). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Lay your @British chicken breasts{2} on the #chopping board{}, place your hand
flat on top and slice into it from the side until there is 2cm left (don't
slice all the way through). Open it up like a book. Repeat for the other
breast(s).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Season the chicken with @salt{} and @pepper{} then lay them in the frying pan.

Cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes} each side. Transfer the chicken to a
#baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven until the chicken is
cooked, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of oil in the now empty frying pan (no need to wash)
over medium-high heat. Add the carrot, stir and cook until softened,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @wholegrain mustard{17%g} and @water{75%ml}. Bring to the boil
then add in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Simmer for ~{2%minutes}, then add the
@baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{105%g} and lentils. Simmer for ~{1%minute} until
piping hot.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove it from the oven and rest for a couple of
minutes.

Slice the chicken into thin strips.

Reheat the lentils if needed (add a splash of water if has become a little dry).

Stir in half the parsley. Spoon the creamy lentils into your #bowls{}. Top with
the chicken slices and a sprinkle of remaining parsley. Enjoy!